reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I sent this back as it was obvious the handles would not withstand much use. You get what you pay for. I'm sure it'd be fine for light use, but I wanted some sturdy utensils for my new SS cookware. The handles are quite long which might be the problem?

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Exactly what I wanted
reviews.reviewText: I needed non porous utensils for health reasons. This set will work well in my kitchen.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice looking utensil set
reviews.reviewText: They arrived in good condition. I washed them by hand and laid they out on a towel to dry. They had water spots on them so I realized I needed to dry them with a towel instead of air dry them. After drying them they looked nice and shiny. They look sturdy and add a nice touch to the kitchen.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars The design is lacking
reviews.reviewText: For the craftsmanship and design I would have expected it to be sold at a lower price. The issue isn’t the actual footing of the tool but the handle. It’s very thin and not comfortable to use over a hot pot or pan. Almost cuts into your skin. Other sets start at $99 and I’ll eventually upgrade and throw it in the goodwill pile. Gets the job done but it makes cooking a chore. Sad because I love to cook.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 1, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Seem like decent enough product but the handles are very short. Not a super high quality product. Also the box it was delivered in was falling apart and very beat up.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 18, 2023
reviews.reviewText: These work wonderfully with my stainless steel pans!
